<paragraph id="B7070862FFDFFFE23CAA9A95F6E2368A" blockId="22.[167,779,160,919]" pageId="22" pageNumber="623">
<emphasis id="85CCD470FFDFFFE23CAA9A95F42837D8" box="[168,778,160,184]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="623" reason="1">
<emphasis id="85CCD470FFDFFFE23CAA9A95F66837D7" bold="true" box="[168,330,160,184]" pageId="22" pageNumber="623">Identification.</emphasis>
Small species of 
<taxonomicName id="70B873E1FFDFFFE23E029A95F54437D7" box="[512,614,160,184]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ambassidae" genus="Ambassis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="623" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="85CCD470FFDFFFE23E029A95F54437D7" box="[512,614,160,184]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="623">Ambassis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(maximum TL
</emphasis>
about 
<quantity id="7040A587FFDFFFE23CE89AF4F60037B6" box="[234,290,193,217]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="623" unit="cm" value="8.0">8 cm</quantity>
); body elongated oval-shaped, laterally compressed; mouth terminal; interrupted lateral line; eye diameter larger than snout length; supraorbital spines 4 or 5; nasal spine present and well developed; posterior margin of preopercle serrated; single dorsal fin deeply notched; dorsal fin spines 7; anal fin spines 3; caudal fin deeply forked; body uniformly pale yellowish with scattered melanophores; fins mostly translucent, first 2 or 3 dorsal fin spines blackish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B7070862FFDFFFE23CCC9BDBF68B34F8" blockId="22.[167,779,160,919]" pageId="22" pageNumber="623">
Tentatively identified as 
<taxonomicName id="70B873E1FFDFFFE23DED9BDBF5E23569" authorityName="Richardson" authorityYear="1846" box="[495,704,494,518]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ambassidae" genus="Ambassis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="623" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vachellii">
<emphasis id="85CCD470FFDFFFE23DED9BDBF5E23569" box="[495,704,494,518]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="623">Ambassis vachellii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
using the identification key of 
<bibRefCitation id="D3297593FFDFFFE23DB1983AF51C3547" author="Allen GR" box="[435,574,527,552]" pageId="22" pageNumber="623" pagination="2433 - 2455" refId="ref26463" refString="Allen GR (1999) Ambassidae (= Chandidae). FAO species identifica- tion guide for fishery purposes. The living marine resources of the Western Central Pacific 4. FAO, Rome, Italy, 2433 - 2455." type="book chapter" year="1999">Allen (1999)</bibRefCitation>
. However, the tax- onomy of small species of 
<taxonomicName id="70B873E1FFDFFFE23DD59804F51F3526" box="[471,573,561,585]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ambassidae" genus="Ambassis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="623" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="85CCD470FFDFFFE23DD59804F51F3526" box="[471,573,561,585]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="623">Ambassis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
having more than one supraorbital spine needs revision. 
<taxonomicName id="70B873E1FFDFFFE23E439867F42B3505" authorityName="Richardson" authorityYear="1846" box="[577,777,594,618]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ambassidae" genus="Ambassis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="623" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vachellii">
<emphasis id="85CCD470FFDFFFE23E439867F42B3505" box="[577,777,594,618]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="623">Ambassis vachellii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can easily be distinguished from the two other species of 
<taxonomicName id="70B873E1FFDFFFE23CC698A0F66A35C2" authorityName="Klunzinger" authorityYear="1870" box="[196,328,661,685]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ambassidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="623" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Ambassidae</taxonomicName>
occurring in Merbok river estuary by the unique combination of two characters: interrupted lateral line and 4 or 5 supraorbital spines. 
<taxonomicName id="70B873E1FFDFFFE23E2A98EDF5D3359F" authorityName="Richardson" authorityYear="1846" box="[552,753,728,752]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ambassidae" genus="Ambassis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="623" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vachellii">
<emphasis id="85CCD470FFDFFFE23E2A98EDF5D3359F" box="[552,753,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="623">Ambassis vachellii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a typical brackish species and the most common species of 
<taxonomicName id="70B873E1FFDFFFE23CC4992EF668345C" authorityName="Klunzinger" authorityYear="1870" box="[198,330,795,819]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ambassidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="623" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Ambassidae</taxonomicName>
in the Merbok river estuary and in other brackish environments in this region (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="D3297593FFDFFFE23E799909F6273419" author="Tongnunui P &amp; Ikejima K &amp; Yamane T &amp; Horinouchi M &amp; Medej T &amp; Sano M &amp; Kurokura H &amp; Taniuchi T" pageId="22" pageNumber="623" pagination="10 - 17" refId="ref28763" refString="Tongnunui P, Ikejima K, Yamane T, Horinouchi M, Medej T, Sano M, Kurokura H, Taniuchi T (2002) Fish fauna of the Sikao Creek mangrove estuary, Trang, Thailand. Fisheries Science 68: 10 - 17. https: // doi. org / 10.1046 / j. 1444 - 2906.2002.00383. x" type="journal article" year="2002">Tongnunui et al. 2002</bibRefCitation>
). Its exact distribution in the Indo-West Pacific region is still unknown.
</paragraph>
